{"type":"message","id":"8edde561","parentId":"a2da394c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:41:31.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z57engyadglz_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 172102\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending TIC Experiment: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Next action is to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) experiment\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. I need to implement a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Analyzes pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (stable, recurring) vs variant (changing, novel)\r\n3. Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to create a script or document that begins implementing the TIC experiment. Since the pulse logs are in `logs/pulse_*.md` format and the most recent one mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-23 171103.md`, I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a TIC experiment implementation\r\n2. Start analyzing the pulse logs for invariants\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's actually in the logs directory and create a concrete implementation.\r\n\r\nI'll create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n- Scans pulse logs\r\n- Identifies invariant patterns (things that repeat across sessions)\r\n- Identifies variant patterns (things that change)\r\n- Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, specific action that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that distinguishes invariants from variants across pulse logs, then measure prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and implements next-pulse prediction. This directly advances the Phase 1 advancement goal and tests the core hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Approach\r\n1. **Invariant Detection**: Content that recurs across multiple pulses = causal/structural\r\n2. **Variant Detection**: Content that changes or appears once = ephemeral/context\r\n3. **Prediction**: Use invariants from pulse N to predict pulse N+1\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation Strategy\r\n- Tokenize pulse content (markdown sections, code blocks, prose)\r\n- Hash each segment for cross-pulse comparison\r\n- Classify by frequency: frequent = invariant, rare = variant\r\n- Test prediction: can invariants from pulse N predict content of pulse N+1?\r\n\r\n## Files to Analyze\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - all pulse logs\r\n- Focus on recent 20 pulses for initial experiment\r\n```\r\n\r\nfile: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env pwsh\r\n# TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinPulseCount = 5,      # Minimum pulses for invariant classification\r\n    [int]$MaxPulses = 20          # How many recent pulses to analyze\r\n)\r\n\r\n$script:Invariants = @{}\r\n$script:Variants = @{}\r\n$script:PulseContent = @()\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem -Path \"logs\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n            Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n            Select-Object -First $MaxPulses\r\n    return $logs\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Tokenize-Pulse {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $tokens = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract markdown sections\r\n    $sections = $Content -split \"(?=^#{1,3}\\s)\" -replace \"^`r?`n\", \"\"\r\n    foreach ($section in $sections) {\r\n        if ($section.Trim()) {\r\n            $tokens += $section.Trim()\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract code blocks\r\n    $codeBlocks = [regex]::Matches($Content, \"```[\\s\\S]*?```\") | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    $tokens += $codeBlocks\r\n    \r\n    return $tokens\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Classify-Content {\r\n    param([string[]]$Tokens)\r\n    \r\n    $frequencies = @{}\r\n    foreach ($token in $Tokens) {\r\n        $hash = (Get-FileHash -InputStream ([IO.MemoryStream]::new([Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($token))) -Algorithm MD5).Hash\r\n        if ($frequencies.ContainsKey($hash)) {\r\n            $frequencies[$hash]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $frequencies[$hash] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $frequencies\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Main {\r\n    Write-Host \"=== TIC Classifier Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n    Write-Host \"Analyzing pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns...\"\r\n    Write-Host \"\"\r\n    \r\n    # Collect all tokens from all pulses\r\n    $allTokens = @()\r\n    $pulseFiles = Get-PulseLogs\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n        $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n        $tokens = Tokenize-Pulse $content\r\n        $allTokens += @{\r\n            File = $file.Name\r\n            Tokens = $tokens\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Count token frequencies across all pulses\r\n    $globalFrequencies = @{}\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $allTokens) {\r\n        foreach ($token in $pulse.Tokens) {\r\n            $hash = (Get-FileHash -InputStream ([IO.MemoryStream]::new\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 17:21:28\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774302091220}}
